column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Tech Mesh 28"
column6:
I was very excited to see these on We Made Too Much and had to buy them. They are very flattering and fit just right around the waist and hips. I'm petite 5'0" and 110 lbs so they are too long. They do a good job of holding everything in place.
They stayed in place for the most part during a yoga class. I only had to adjust the waist after it folded down a couple times. I don't know if I would have gotten too hot in them if it was a heated class. They were ok to walk outside in on a 40 degree day.
Downside- They arrived dirty. They had some white streaks on them.

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Tech Mesh 28"
column6: These pants were exactly how I expected them to look! Super cute, nice material, good quality. But, they are sized very small. I love the fit, but maybe order a size up. Lulu sizing is different. Love these overall, the mesh adds a nice contrast. Good buy! :)

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Tech Mesh 28"
column6:
I love the WunderUnder leggings I've purchased in the past,
I was excited to try these limited edition style that could add a little flair to my legging collection. I washed them before wearing them to the gym, and I wore them to a training session that incorporated a lot of different movements. Here are the pros: Cute color (dark chrome) upon receiving them I realized a have a lulu bra in the same color and now I have a matching set. Material is soft. cute design
Cons: Color shows sweat around crotch (no wicking here ladies) Material is THICK, I mean I will put them on in summer and immediately start sweating. Stitching around mesh panels is THICK. Every time I am on my belly doing a movement I can just feel it cutting into my legs. Waist band slips more than my other WunderUNDERs. I am 5'4, the length is great on me, I weigh 146, I ordered a 6 and the size is perfect. I'm sure they will go to the bottom of my legging pile during the summer, such a bummer for the price paid! I would stick with the original Wunder Under design if you are thinking of adding another pair to your collection. If I could exchange them I would in a heart beat.
